HEADWORD: Cosecant
<hw>Co*se"cant</hw> <pr>(k?-s?"k?nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[For
<ets>co. secans</ets>, an abbrev. of L. <ets>complementi
secans</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Trig.)</fld> <def>The secant of the
complement of an arc or angle. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Functions</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

